ENTRY       EC 2.7.8.35                 Enzyme
NAME        UDP-N-acetylglucosamine---decaprenyl-phosphate N-acetylglucosaminephosphotransferase;
            GlcNAc-1-phosphate transferase;
            UDP-GlcNAc:undecaprenyl phosphate GlcNAc-1-phosphate transferase;
            WecA;
            WecA transferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring phosphorus-containing groups;
            Transferases for other substituted phosphate groups
SYSNAME     UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine:trans,octacis-decaprenyl-phosphate N-acetylglucosaminephosphotransferase
REACTION    UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine + trans,octacis-decaprenyl phosphate = UMP + N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-diphospho-trans,octacis-decaprenol [RN:R10137]
ALL_REAC    R10137
SUBSTRATE   UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine [CPD:C00043];
            trans,octacis-decaprenyl phosphate [CPD:C02970]
PRODUCT     UMP [CPD:C00105];
            N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-diphospho-trans,octacis-decaprenol [CPD:C20390]
COMMENT     Isolated from Mycobacterium tuberculosis and Mycobacterium smegmatis. This enzyme catalyses the synthesis of monotrans,octacis-decaprenyl-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl diphosphate (mycobacterial lipid I), an essential lipid intermediate for the biosynthesis of various bacterial cell envelope components. cf. EC 2.7.8.33, UDP-GlcNAc:undecaprenyl-phosphate GlcNAc-1-phosphate transferase.
HISTORY     EC 2.7.8.35 created 2012
